President Biden visited the Volvo Group Powertrain Operations Facility in Hagerstown, Maryland and delivered a speech highlighting the importance of American manufacturing and the need for government investments in infrastructure and clean energy. He emphasized his support for unions and praised the workers for their dedication and skill. The President discussed the achievements of his administration, such as job creation and reducing healthcare costs, and criticized Republicans for opposing his policies. He warned that if Republicans regain control of Congress, they would roll back the progress made on issues like prescription drug prices, healthcare, and Social Security. President Biden urged Americans to choose a future that prioritizes the working class and invests in a sustainable economy.